value representing the rest of the computation of the program. "What to do next" is precisely what has to be explicitly encoded in order  to program non trivial web interactions. Continuations allow web applications  to be written in direct style that is, as a single program that displays  forms and reads form submission since continuations automatically capture  everything (control point, lexical bindings, etc.) that is needed to resume  the computation. Programming is therefore safer, easier and more re-usable.</p><p><u>Downloads:</u></p><ul><li><a href="http://www-spi.lip6.fr/~queinnec/Papers/www.ps.gz">ps</a></li><li><a href="http://www-spi.lip6.fr/~queinnec/PDF/www.pdf">pdf</a></li></ul><p><u>Bibtex citation:</u></p><pre>@techreport{
   key = "Que:Que2001a"
   author = "Christian Queinnec"
